Description: Ostracon (?) on fragment of a limestone artefact with incised characters.
Curator's comments: It is one of nine fragments of limestone bearing some incised charachers: BM 1885,1101.557-565 (see also BM 1885,1101.429). The register indicates the Hellenion as the findspot for these objects found in 1885. It is most likely the Great Temenos, since the Hellenion was only discovered by Hogarth in 1899 and Petrie had misinterpreted the Great Temenos for the Hellenion.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (BC.07)
